# paw — AI SDLC rules for Cursor

You have access to specialized agent definitions in the `agents/` directory. Reference them when the task matches their specialty.

## Git rules (enforced)

- Always `git pull` (merge, not rebase) before push
- Never `git rebase` against published history
- Never `git push --force`
- Never commit to `main` directly — use a feature branch
- Always verify `git branch` before committing

## Code rules

- Tests before or alongside code. Never after.
- No silent failures — every catch block must log or re-throw.
- No secrets in source code — use environment variables.
- Validate input at boundaries. Encode output for context.

